  <content>This macro allows to add a translation link, which will then be used to translate any HTML block in a wiki page. The macro can be added inline or as a block.

**Usage**

|=Parameter|=Mandatory|=Description|=Default value
|##cssSelector##|Yes|{{velocity}}$services.localization.render('rendering.macro.deeplTranslation.parameter.cssSelector.description'){{/velocity}}|//N/A//
|##classSelector##|No|{{velocity}}$services.localization.render('rendering.macro.deeplTranslation.parameter.classSelector.description'){{/velocity}}|//N/A//
|##extraCssClasses##|No|{{velocity}}$services.localization.render('rendering.macro.deeplTranslation.parameter.classSelector.description'){{/velocity}}|//N/A//

**Example**

(% class="myTestTranslation" %)
(((
This is a text in english. If you access this page with the wiki configured in another language, you should see a translate link appearing below.
)))

{{deeplTranslation cssSelector=".myTestTranslation"/}}</content>
